                    <msContents>
                        <summary>The document is an agreement and may be dealing with a sale. What remains are fragments of the signatures of apparently two parties to a contract, a short signature by a witness, and the signature of the public notary. One of the parties may be Kyra, daughter of Georgios. It was found next to 42 and 43.</summary>
                        <msItemStruct>
                            <note type="general">Written transversa charta. Only the bottom margin (10 cm) is extant. The document contains four different hands: signatures of the two parties (m1 and m2) and signatures by a witness (m3) and the public notary (m4).</note>
                            <note type="general">Reproduced in plates LXIV</note>
